The Telegraph - Calcutta : Bengal

 Garden closed

 Alipurduar, April 17: A Dooars tea estate downed shutters a day after workers assaulted its manager. 

 Kartik Tea Estate today became the 16th garden to shut down in the region. 

 The management was supposed to pay the workers a part of the salary for the past three months, ration and other dues on Saturday. Police said the workers gheraoed manager Bapan Bhawal after nothing was paid till Monday.




